ğŸ“– Project Overview

In cybersecurity, prioritization matters more than volume. Organizations face thousands of vulnerabilities daily, but not all pose equal risk. This project focuses on:

Understanding why prioritization is critical

Exploring the official CVE database

Researching real-world vulnerabilities in common software

Documenting impact, risk, and importance

ğŸ¯ Objectives

Learn the importance of vulnerability prioritization

Explore and understand the CVE (Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures) database

Analyze 3 real-world vulnerabilities

Document:

What the vulnerability is

What impact it has

Why it matters

ğŸ” Why Prioritization Matters More Than Volume

Organizations often discover hundreds or thousands of vulnerabilities, but:

Not all vulnerabilities are exploitable

Not all have high impact

Resources are limited

âœ… Key Reasons

Risk Reduction: Focus on vulnerabilities that can cause the most damage

Efficient Use of Resources: Fixing high-risk issues first saves time and cost

Business Protection: Prevents system downtime, financial loss, and data breaches

Better Security Posture: Reduces the attack surface

ğŸ¯ Example

Fixing 1 critical vulnerability is often more valuable than fixing 50 low-risk vulnerabilities.

